  "text": "Some of the studies have used discrete Fourier transform (DFT) to extract frequency domain features from the ECG signal. Jerritta et al. [CITATION_1] discuss the advantages of using frequency domain features compared to EMD based features. They claim that, unlike EMD features that provide an idea about the local properties of the ECG wave, the DFT method provides information about the frequency content of the signal. In their study, they have achieved 54% accuracy for recognizing neutral, happiness, sadness, fear, surprise and disgust emotions from ECG signals utilizing DFT based features of ten intrinsic mode functions derived from the EMD method.",
